106. Municipal Accountant:

Prepare the JEV to record the beginning balance of the local road network and its components in the general ledger and the Local RN Ledger Card (Annex D of the Circular), respectively;

Support the JEV with the Registry of Public Infrastructures for Roads, working paper on the distribution of costs for the road components, and working paper on the determination of the depreciated replacement cost for road components with no available cost per registry;

Keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every RN; and

Prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year.

Recommendations
We recommended, and Management agreed that:
The Municipal Mayor, after affixing the Box D of DVs and checks, to forward the same to the MTO for releasing of checks;
The MTO to immediately submit to the accounting office the unsubmitted DVs together with their complete supporting documents;
The Accounting Office to recheck all DVs which have been returned from the MTO for any changes i.e., cancelled or revisions, and make necessary adjustments if needed; and
Strictly comply with the prescribed laws, rules and regulations on the prompt submission of the financial transactions and reports with complete documentation as basis in establishing the validity and regularity of the payments made and occurrence of the transactions recorded in the books of accounts.

Recommendations
6.12	We recommended and the Management agreed on the following:
Coordinate with the Province on Road Lots and identify the road lots belonging to the Municipality; and trace documents for the acquisitions to determine ownership of road lots;
The Municipal Engineer to reconcile its records on RN with the records of Accounting, and MGSO, and ensure that it is  complete with description and cost segregation of road components including road lots, road pavement, drainage and slope protection structures and other miscellaneous structures;
The Municipal Accountant to record the cost of road lots upon receipt of information from the Municipal Engineer on road description.
The Inventory Committee to prepare the Physical Count of the RN System of the Municipality using the pro-forma schedule in Annex C of COA Circular No. 2015-008;
The MGSO to:
Render a Report on RN using the pro-forma schedule in Annex A;
Maintain a local road inventory, Road Map and complete RN Property Card for all roads and its components; and
Submit those road networks with complete supporting documents for the Municipal Accountant to record it.

Prepare internal rules in the adoption of electronic signatures in accordance with COA Circular No. 2021-006 that include, among others, the following:

25. Designation of focal person for all matters pertaining to electronic signing implementation of the LGU;

26. Development, maintenance, and updating of the system documentation used for creating electronic records with signatures;

27. Development, maintenance, and implementation of standard operating procedures for the creation, utilization, storage, security, and management of electronic records that contain signatures, to ensure that the records are protected from unauthorized alteration or destruction;
Implementation of security awareness program such as training the employees on the acceptable use of signature on electronic documents; and

28. Guidelines with regard to the scope of the employee’s authority to use electronic documents; and sanction for misuse or abuse of signatures.

29. To strengthen the risk management capabilities of the Municipal Government and enable it to manage its vulnerabilities in the event of disruptive events, we recommended that the Municipal Mayor shall  institutionalize the PSCP by creating a working group that will perform the following activities:

a. to conduct risk assessment; 
b. to identify critical processes and functions; 
c. to determine scenarios that may disrupt normal operation; 
d. to conduct risk analysis and impact analysis; 
e. to formulate the PSCP based on the identified risks on critical processes and functions and its related steps to be followed to eliminate, if not mitigate, the impact of the determined disruptions following the prescribed template and be guided by the PSCP guidebook; and

30. To submit plan to the MDRRMO for review, to the Municipal Mayor for approval, and to the Sangguniang Bayan for the passage of a resolution to institutionalize the PSCP.

We recommended for Management to:

32. Direct the Municipal Engineering Office to prepare and maintain a monthly monitoring report to keep track of the progress of all PPAs specially those that involved infrastructure projects within its jurisdiction from planning to its completion stage;

33. Assign Project Heads/Managers to all non-infrastructure PPAs to prepare and consolidate a Monthly Monitoring Report;

34. Direct the Municipal Engineering Office and the assigned Project Heads/Managers to coordinate with the Municipal Accountant on the costs incurred in each PPAs as basis in the preparation of their Monthly Monitoring Report which should be submitted to COA at least on a quarterly basis; and

35. Require the Municipal Engineering Office and the assigned Project Heads/Manager to strictly adhere to the provisions of COA Circular No. 2013-004.

Immediately submit the documents of the projects enumerated in Appendix C to facilitate technical review and inspection;

Stop the practice of submitting lacking documents and strictly comply with the submission requirements prescribed in COA Circular No. 2009-001 to effect timeliness of the technical review and inspection process; and 

Review the existing workload of the focal person considering that her current designation affects her responsibility in the submission of project documents to the Office of the Auditor and to fast track the review of contracts and inspection of completed projects of the Municipality.

